SBN|978-1-85065-868-9}}\n* Stevenson, Francis Seymour. ''A History of Montenegro'' 2002) {{ISBN|978-1-4212-5089-2}}\n* \u00d6zcan, U\u011fur ''[http://www.ttk.gov.tr/index.php?Page=Yayinlar&KitapNo=989 II. Abdulhamid D\u00f6nemi Osmanl\u0131-Karada\u011f Siyasi \u0130li\u015fkileri]'' [Political relations between the Ottoman Empire and Montenegro in the Abdul Hamid II era] (2013) [https://web.archive.org/web/20130328034059/http://www.ttk.org.tr/index.php?Page=Anasayfa&Lisan=en T\u00fcrk Tarih Kurumu] Turkish Historical Society {{ISBN|978-975-16-2527-4}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Sister project links|Montenegro|voy=Montenegro}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100427004815/http://www.gov.me/en/homepage Official website of the Government of Montenegro (English)]\n* {{CIA World Factbook link|mj|Montenegro}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120830120309/http://ucblibraries.colorado.edu/govpubs/for/montenegro.htm Montenegro] from ''UCB Libraries GovPubs''\n* {{curlie|Regional/Europe/Montenegro}}\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-17667132 Montenegro profile] from the [[BBC News]]\n* [http://www.culture-corner.me/?jezik=ENG Culture Corner \u2013 leading Montenegrin web portal for culture]\n* [http://www.nparkovi.me/ Official Website National Parks Montenegro]\n* {{Wikiatlas|Montenegro}}\n* {{osmrelation-inline|53296|bullet=no}}\n{{Municipalities of Montenegro}}\n{{Geographical regions of Montenegro}}\n{{Ethnic groups of Montenegro}}\n{{Montenegrin universities}}\n{{Navboxes\n| list=\n{{Sovereign states of Europe}}\n{{Balkan countries}}\n{{Council of Europe}}\n{{North Atlantic Treaty Organization}}\n{{European Union candidates}}\n{{Central European Free Trade Agreement}}\n{{OSCE}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Montenegro| ]]<!--please leave the empty space as standard-->\n[[Category:2006 establishments in Montenegro|*]]\n[[Category:Balkan countries]]\n[[Category:Countries in Europe]]\n[[Category:Member states of NATO]]\n[[Category:Member 